<dl id="un1013e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013e"> (NLI.3) 13(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tantras = rules for Theugical cult of the deities <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un1013e"> <li>Ulysses unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The &ldquo;cult of the left hand&rdquo; is, however, best known as a technical term in India, in use among the T&amacr;ntrikas, or practisers of the Tantras. <mark>The Tantras</mark> (= Doctrines, Rules) are religious treatises teaching magical and mystical <mark>formularies for the theurgical cult of the deities</mark>, or the attainment of superhuman powers; they are mostly in the form of dialogues between Shiva, the Great Yogin of the Gods, and his Shakti, Spouse or Power, Durg&amacr;. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. M., &ldquo;Queries and Notes. VI&rdquo; 368</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07255i" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07255i">VI.C.07:255(i)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
